d.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"0598b281-0286-4b2c-891c-cc5b4c94ba24","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"BLOCKER ASSESSMENT (2026-07-17, agent): E5 is BLOCKED on R5 (ea39, status=open, NOT landed) — cannot be completed independently. Evidence: (1) all 4 of E5's ACs reference R5's candidate change — AC1 'runs the amended kernel', AC2 'diff EMPTY: byte-identical (decision,priority,validity)' is inherently baseline-vs-amended, AC3 'the new sub-answer is na outside the G6/E4/T3 cohort'. (2) R5's amendment is absent from code: grep 'asserted_capability_confirmed' src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/ returns nothing. (3) Scope explicitly reads 'src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/ (candidate branch build)' — that candidate branch does not exist yet. Unlike E2/E3 (harness+corpus+baseline, candidate later), E5 IS the candidate-vs-baseline diff: a self-vs-self replay of today's kernel would trivially be empty and prove nothing, and would FAIL the completion verifier (AC3 cites a sub-answer absent from the codebase). Spend note: E5 itself is LOW-spend when unblocked (deterministic replay of pass-3 math in src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/decide.py — validity()/priority=validity*impact/decision core; plus a ~20-finding live sanity slice). Corpus docs/experiments/code_review_adjudication.jsonl (161 lines) is present. RECOMMENDATION: schedule E5 immediately AFTER R5's candidate change exists on a branch; leave E5 open/unclaimed until then.","timestamp":1784342969931607001}],"created_at":1784143762473631001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[],"description":"## Why\nR5 changes the review_kernel verification vocabulary, which is SHARED with the code-review gate. The epic's gate row demands proof that code-review decisions are untouched before any kernel change lands - a silent cross-gate regression is the worst failure mode of this epic.\n\n## What\nCross-gate non-regression replay: run the R5-amended kernel (asserted_capability_confirmed sub-answer added) over the existing code-review adjudication corpus (docs/experiments/code_review_adjudication.jsonl) and require BYTE-IDENTICAL decisions: every finding's (decision, priority, validity) unchanged, and the new sub-answer reads na everywhere outside the G6/E4/T3 cohort. Deterministic replay of pass-2/3 math over recorded verifications - no live LLM needed for the decision comparison; a small live sanity slice (~20 findings) confirms the amended prompt still parses.\n\n## Scope\n- docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/ (replay driver + runs/ diff output + writeup).\n- Reads src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/ (candidate branch build); no packaged changes land from this story.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The replay runs the amended kernel over the full code_review_adjudication.jsonl corpus and commits a decision diff artifact.\n- [ ] The diff is EMPTY: byte-identical (decision, priority, validity) for every code-review finding; any non-empty diff fails the gate and is recorded as an R5 blocker.\n- [ ] The new sub-answer is na for every finding outside the G6/E4/T3 cohort, asserted by the replay artifact.\n- [ ] A docs/experiments/ writeup records method and outcome (the input to R5's gate row).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/","reason":"cross-gate replay driver"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","6982-2e75-f8fa-43b9"]],"parent_id":"6982-2e75-f8fa-43b9","parent_status_uuid":"0f2052d1-78e6-4c8d-9625-d33e7348db21","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts